problem_text: \overrightarrow B A and \overrightarrow B C are opposite rays and \overrightarrow B D bisects \angle A B F. If m \angle F B C = 2 x + 25 and m \angle A B F = 10 x - 1, find m \angle D B F.
compact_text: \overrightarrow BA and \overrightarrow BC are opposite rays and \overrightarrow BD bisects \angle ABF. If m \angle FBC = 2x+25 and m \angle ABF = 10x-1, find m \angle DBF.
annotat_text: $\overrightarrow{BA}$ and $\overrightarrow{BC}$ are opposite rays and $\overrightarrow{BD}$ bisects $\angle ABF$. If $m \angle FBC=2x+25$ and $m \angle ABF=10x-1$, find $m \angle DBF$.
